        <abstract> 
<p>CD asks his father to consider the offer of the <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> voyage once more. He encloses his list of RWD’s objections and Josiah Wedgwood’s responses [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">109</hi>]. Asks his father to give him a decided answer: if "no" he will never again mention the subject.</p> 
